After completing this lesson, you will be able to:

After completing this lesson, you will be able to:

use the SAP BTP deployment environment (Cloud Foundry)

Deploy and Run App

Deploy app

Before deploying, you must have a build showing as delivered.

  1. Click Deploy MTA.

  2. Select the https://api.cf.us10.hana.ondemand.com environment from the dropdown. Click Authorize BTP Deployments.

  3. You will get a dialog for signing in to the deployment environment (Cloud Foundry). Enter academy-platform and click the Sign in with alternative identity provider button.

  4. Click Authorize.

  5. Once signed in, select the Cloud Foundry deployment details:

    • Organization: sap-build-academy-us10
    • Space: AC_SAPBUILD

  6. Click Deploy MTA TO AC_SAPBUILD.

  7. The screen will show a running list of log messages this could take about 2 minutes.

  8. Once it is done, you will get a screen like this:

    The name of the app is at the end of the URL.

Run app

  1. Open the deployment URL.

  2. You should now see your application.
